WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:15.260 --> 00:00:19.260
I'm standing in front of you today

00:00:19.260 --> 00:00:21.260
in all humility,

00:00:21.260 --> 00:00:23.260
wanting to share with you

00:00:23.260 --> 00:00:26.260
my journey of the last six years

00:00:26.260 --> 00:00:28.260
in the field of service

00:00:28.260 --> 00:00:30.260
and education.

00:00:30.260 --> 00:00:33.260
And I'm not a trained academic.

00:00:33.260 --> 00:00:36.260
Neither am I a veteran social worker.

00:00:36.260 --> 00:00:39.260
I was 26 years in the corporate world,

00:00:39.260 --> 00:00:42.260
trying to make organizations profitable.

00:00:42.260 --> 00:00:44.260
And then in 2003

00:00:44.260 --> 00:00:48.260
I started Parikrma Humanity Foundation

00:00:48.260 --> 00:00:50.260
from my kitchen table.

00:00:50.260 --> 00:00:54.260
The first thing that we did was walk through the slums.

00:00:54.260 --> 00:00:57.260
You know, by the way, there are two million people

00:00:57.260 --> 00:01:02.260
in Bangalore, who live in 800 slums.

00:01:02.260 --> 00:01:05.260
We couldn't go to all the slums,

00:01:05.260 --> 00:01:07.260
but we tried to cover as much as we could.

00:01:07.260 --> 00:01:09.260
We walked through these slums,

00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:14.260
identified houses where children would never go to school.

00:01:14.260 --> 00:01:16.260
We talked to the parents,

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:20.260
tried to convince them about sending their children to school.

00:01:20.260 --> 00:01:22.260
We played with the children,

00:01:22.260 --> 00:01:25.260
and came back home really tired,

00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:28.260
exhausted, but with images

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:31.260
of bright faces, twinkling eyes,

00:01:31.260 --> 00:01:34.260
and went to sleep.

00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:37.260
We were all excited to start,

00:01:37.260 --> 00:01:41.260
but the numbers hit us then:

00:01:41.260 --> 00:01:43.260
200 million children

00:01:43.260 --> 00:01:45.260
between four to 14 that

00:01:45.260 --> 00:01:47.260
should be going to school, but do not;

00:01:47.260 --> 00:01:49.260
100 million children

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:52.260
who go to school but cannot read;

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:57.260
125 million who cannot do basic maths.

00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:02.260
We also heard that 250 billion Indian rupees

00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:05.260
was dedicated for government schooling.

00:02:05.260 --> 00:02:08.260
Ninety percent of it was spent on teachers' salary

00:02:08.260 --> 00:02:10.260
and administrators' salary.

00:02:10.260 --> 00:02:12.260
And yet, India has nearly

00:02:12.260 --> 00:02:15.260
the highest teacher absenteeism

00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:17.260
in the world,

00:02:17.260 --> 00:02:19.260
with one out of four teachers

00:02:19.260 --> 00:02:23.260
not going to school at all the entire academic year.

00:02:23.260 --> 00:02:27.260
Those numbers were absolutely mind-boggling,

00:02:27.260 --> 00:02:30.260
overwhelming, and we were constantly asked,

00:02:30.260 --> 00:02:33.260
"When will you start? How many schools will you start?

00:02:33.260 --> 00:02:35.260
How many children will you get?

00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:37.260
How are you going to scale?

00:02:37.260 --> 00:02:39.260
How are you going to replicate?"

00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:43.260
It was very difficult not to get scared, not to get daunted.

00:02:43.260 --> 00:02:45.260
But we dug our heels

00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:48.260
and said, "We're not in the number game.

00:02:48.260 --> 00:02:52.260
We want to take one child at a time

00:02:52.260 --> 00:02:55.260
and take the child right through school,

00:02:55.260 --> 00:02:57.260
sent to college,

00:02:57.260 --> 00:03:01.260
and get them prepared for better living,

00:03:01.260 --> 00:03:04.260
a high value job."

00:03:04.260 --> 00:03:07.260
So, we started Parikrma.

00:03:07.260 --> 00:03:09.260
The first Parikrma school

00:03:09.260 --> 00:03:11.260
started in a slum

00:03:11.260 --> 00:03:14.260
where there were 70,000 people

00:03:14.260 --> 00:03:17.260
living below the poverty line.

00:03:17.260 --> 00:03:20.260
Our first school was

00:03:20.260 --> 00:03:25.260
on a rooftop of a building inside the slums,

00:03:25.260 --> 00:03:27.260
a second story building, the only second story building

00:03:27.260 --> 00:03:29.260
inside the slums.

00:03:29.260 --> 00:03:32.260
And that rooftop did not have

00:03:32.260 --> 00:03:36.260
any ceiling, only half a tin sheet.

00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:40.260
That was our first school. One hundred sixty-five children.

00:03:40.260 --> 00:03:42.260
Indian academic year begins in June.

00:03:42.260 --> 00:03:45.260
So, June it rains, so many a times

00:03:45.260 --> 00:03:48.260
all of us would be huddled under the tin roof,

00:03:48.260 --> 00:03:50.260
waiting for the rain to stop.

00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:55.260
My God! What a bonding exercise that was.

00:03:55.260 --> 00:03:57.260
And all of us

00:03:57.260 --> 00:04:01.260
that were under that roof are still here together today.

00:04:01.260 --> 00:04:03.260
Then came the second school,

00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:06.260
the third school, the fourth school

00:04:06.260 --> 00:04:08.260
and a junior college.

00:04:08.260 --> 00:04:11.260
In six years now,

00:04:11.260 --> 00:04:14.260
we have four schools, one junior college,

00:04:14.260 --> 00:04:16.260
1,100 children

00:04:16.260 --> 00:04:18.260
coming from 28 slums

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:20.260
and four orphanages.

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:23.260
(Applause)

00:04:23.260 --> 00:04:26.260
Our dream is very simple:

00:04:26.260 --> 00:04:29.260
to send each of these kids, get them prepared

00:04:29.260 --> 00:04:32.260
to be educated

00:04:32.260 --> 00:04:34.260
but also to live peacefully,

00:04:34.260 --> 00:04:37.260
contented in this conflict-ridden

00:04:37.260 --> 00:04:41.260
chaotic globalized world.

00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:43.260
Now, when you talk global

00:04:43.260 --> 00:04:45.260
you have to talk English.

00:04:45.260 --> 00:04:47.260
And so all our schools

00:04:47.260 --> 00:04:50.260
are English medium schools.

00:04:50.260 --> 00:04:52.260
But they know there is this myth

00:04:52.260 --> 00:04:54.260
that children from the slums

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:57.260
cannot speak English well.

00:04:57.260 --> 00:04:59.260
No one in their family has spoken English.

00:04:59.260 --> 00:05:03.260
No one in their generation has spoken English.

00:05:03.260 --> 00:05:05.260
But how wrong it is.

